{
  "texts": [
    "• Notes are denoted by the letters a-g (for notes in the octave above middle C) and A-G (for the octave below).",
    "• Note duration is given by appending a number.",
    "For instance, A2 indicates a note twice the default length.",
    "• Sharps, naturals, and flats are shown with ˆ, =, and _.",
    "For example, ˆF is an F sharp."
  ]
}